>> source: https://recipe.awesomedrinks.com/recipe/brooklyn/

Add @rye whiskey{60%ml}, @dry vermouth{30%ml}, @Maraschino liqueur{7.5%ml}, @orange bitters{3%dash} to a #mixing glass{} and stir for up to ~{2 minutes} until well chilled.

Strain into a chilled #martini glass{} and serve. 

-- The original recipe calls for Amer Picon or angostura bitters, but the most reasonable substitution is orange bitters because it is widely available.
